{{sources|date=Dec 2011}}

[[Image:'Sculpture', iron sculpture by Ezra Orion (Israeli), 1966, Israel Museum, Jerusalem, Israel.JPG|thumb|right|150px|'Sculpture', iron sculpture by Ezra Orion, 1966, [[Israel Museum]], [[Jerusalem, Israel]]]]

'''Ezra Orion''' (born 1934) is an Israeli artist who was born in [[Beit Alfa|Kibbutz Beit-Alfa]] and grew up in [[Ramat Yohanan|Kibutz Ramat-Yohanan]]. 

==Biography==
He attended the [[Bezalel Academy of Art and Design]] in [[Jerusalem]], and from 1964 to 1967, he attended the [[Central Saint Martins College of Art and Design]] and the [[Royal College of Art]] in London.  

Orion describes his geologic structures as <U+201C>launching pads<U+201D> for the mind.  In the late 1980s, he executed an "Intergalactic Sculpture" by sending a [[Laser]] beam to the [[Milky Way]] under the auspices of the [[Israeli Space Agency]] and the [[Israel Museum]].

==Sources==
* Orion, Ezra, Sculpture in the Solar System: From Geologically Based Earthworks to Astro-Sculpture in ''Leonardo'', Vol. 18, No. 3 (1985), pp.&nbsp;157<U+2013>160.
* Zaslmona, Ygal, ''Ezra Orion/Tectonic Sculpture, Yeda Sela, 1982.

